name: Conjuro °_°
description:
Submit to her spell /
forgetting to lie /
What haunts is the risk /
The lure of the unknown /
The effect of the mysterious /
No everyday approach can disclose /
except in the truth of question /
Away from the conventional flow /
of every thing /
where all the horses of Rome are bound /
Captured /
corrupted by cold and white snow. /
Her old method of dealing, so slow /
it becomes a flare /
like thoughts folding down through the years /
still the long, drawn out plan /
of a slow destruction /
Divine and pure beyond the telling /
Her long deep phoenix bend of flame, /
and the ending that came with a wave /
replenishing her art with every winter. /
All she can take part in as swallows /
in their own ruins. /
To pass and to pass and to pass again. /
The manor built and described, /
where the plume of his soul disbursed. /
Not the eyes /
Sad, the violins; /
A motion so slow /
The sense and sane memory repeat: /
Her long deep phoenix bend of flame, /
And the ending that came with a wave. /
Replenishing her art with every winter. /
All she can take part in as swallows /
In their own ruins. /
